<br>
Axe gets 15% bonus against leather<br>
-10% against studded<br>
-10% against chain<br>
-5% against plate<br>
<br>
numbers may not be completely accurate<br>
<br>
Hammer gets +10% against studded<br>
+10% against plate<br>
<br>
...I'm not exactly sure what Mythic was thinking when creating the slashing damage tables.<br>
An additional +10-20% against cloth for Axe would balance it out nicely..and would cause many skalds to stay axe. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#d1c2a2><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub36.ezboard.com/udarkith.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Darkith</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Team Skald Member</span><br>  Posts: 37<br> <font color=#ff0000>(5/3/02 12:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub36.ezboard.com/fteamskaldfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=15>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://asgarthvanguard.com/images/avcrest.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Increased viability of parry skill.</span><hr size=1> Chain: 15% resistant to slash (most blades and most high level arrows), 15% sensitive to thrust (spears, some arrows, and some blades), 10% resistant to heat, 10% sensitive to energy  <br>
  <br>
Plate: 10% sensitive to crush (hammers, maces), 5% resistant to thrust, 5% resistant to slash, 10% resistant to heat, 10% sensitive to cold, 10% sensitive to energy  <br>
  <br>
Studded: 10% sensitive to crush, 10% resistant to thrust, 10% resistant to heat, 5% sensitive to cold, 5% sensitive to energy  <br>
  <br>
Leather: 15% sensitive to slash, 15% resistant to thrust; 15% sensitive to heat, 10% resistant to cold  <br>
  <br>
Cloth: no resistances or sensitivities <br>
<br>
<br>
Anyone know scale? <p>-----------------------------------<br>
